.TH "devm_platform_get_irqs_affinity" 9 "devm_platform_get_irqs_affinity" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
devm_platform_get_irqs_affinity \- devm method to get a set of IRQs for a device using an interrupt affinity descriptor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" devm_platform_get_irqs_affinity
.BI "(struct platform_device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct irq_affinity *affd "  ","
.BI "unsigned int minvec "  ","
.BI "unsigned int maxvec "  ","
.BI "int **irqs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
platform device pointer
.IP "affd" 12
affinity descriptor
.IP "minvec" 12
minimum count of interrupt vectors
.IP "maxvec" 12
maximum count of interrupt vectors
.IP "irqs" 12
pointer holder for IRQ numbers
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Gets a set of IRQs for a platform device, and updates IRQ afffinty according
to the passed affinity descriptor
.SH "RETURN"
Number of vectors on success, negative error number on failure.
